nload PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_5752408\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_5752408\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 23, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bqo1704690930619.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bqo1704690930619.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bqo1704690930619.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"oyw1665702656799\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Uniface Component Types\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface components handle most of the processing of a Uniface application. The different types of Uniface component are intended for different platforms and serve different functions.\n </p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"oyw1665702656799__note_w0ab1b5b1_w1ab1b5_w2ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> All components share the same component\n         namespace, so component names must be unique, regardless of the type of component. For\n         example, it is not possible to have a Dynamic Server Page and a Form called\n         PURCHASE_ORDER.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oyw1665702656799__p_d10907e1_d10908e1_d10909e1\">Components for the user interface of web and mobile apps:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"oyw1665702656799__li_d5048e1_d5049e1_d5050e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ull1704691217498.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ull1704691217498.html\" title=\"Dynamic Server Pages(DSP) components define the user interface of web pages that can be incrementally and dynamically updated. They can be used in rich interactive web applications and in cross-platform mobile apps.\">Dynamic Server Pages</a>—interactive pages for incrementally and dynamically displaying and updating data in a web or mobile environment.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"oyw1665702656799__li_d5051e1_d5052e1_d5053e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"snh1704692180687.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/snh1704692180687.html\" title=\"Static Server Page (USP) components generate a complete web page every time they are activated. This makes them useful for relatively static web pages or a thin-client architecture in which all processing is done on the server. They can also be used for RESTful applications or file upload functionality.\">Static Server Pages</a>—interactive pages for displaying and updating data in a web environment. The web pages are processed as complete pages.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oyw1665702656799__p_d10910e1_d10911e1_d10912e1\">Components for the presentation layer of desktop applications:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"oyw1665702656799__li_d5054e1_d5055e1_d5056e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"usl1704692305727.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/usl1704692305727.html\" title=\"Form components provide the user interface for Uniface desktop applications. They are always executed on the client system and can be modal (form retains focus until it is closed) or non-modal (users can switch focus to other forms).\">Forms</a> —interactive screens for displaying and updating data in a desktop environment.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"oyw1665702656799__li_d5060e1_d5061e1_d5062e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ccr1704692448139.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ccr1704692448139.html\" title=\"Reports are components for generating output—they have no user interface and cannot update the database. They make use of headers, footers, and break frames to format data and control printing.\">Reports</a> —layouts for presenting data in a printed output.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oyw1665702656799__p_d10913e1_d10914e1_d10915e1\">Components for the business logic and data layers:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"oyw1665702656799__li_d5063e1_d5064e1_d5065e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cgf1704692857485.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cgf1704692857485.html\" title=\"Service components are designed to handle most Uniface application processing. They usually group together those entities that are needed to support the processing of a business object, such as an order or a customer. For example, an order update service could combine entities used to update both customer and order entities.\">Services</a>—components without a user interface that contain operations that can be used locally or remotely.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"oyw1665702656799__li_d5066e1_d5067e1_d5068e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sqn1704693127922.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sqn1704693127922.html\" title=\"Session service components define task-specific behavior for components in the presentation tier. For example, a user enters information to update a customer using a dynamic server page, but a session service is called to actually perform the data update.\">Session Services</a>—service components that manage task-specific behavior, complex business behavior, transactions, and referential integrity. Session services centralize complex business rules affecting multiple data entities.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"oyw1665702656799__li_d5069e1_d5070e1_d5071e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ypz1704693534790.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ypz1704693534790.html\" title=\"Entity services implement simple business rules upon a single entity. They hide business logic and database access from the visible presentation component, acting as an intermediary component between the entity and the database.\">Entity Services</a>—service components that centralize simple business rules for single data entities.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ifc1665702608950.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Component</a><p>A Component is a Main Development Object that defines an executable part of an application. It defines the data structure used to access data, the layout (if applicable) used to present it, and the actions used to modify, validate, and store data.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5752408\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5752408\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Uniface Component Types Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 23, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uniface Component Types Uniface components handle most of the processing of a Uniface application. The different types of Uniface component are intended for different platforms and serve different functions. Note: All components share the same component namespace, so component names must be unique, regardless of the type of component. For example, it is not possible to have a Dynamic Server Page and a Form called PURCHASE_ORDER. Components for the user interface of web and mobile apps: Dynamic Server Pages —interactive pages for incrementally and dynamically displaying and updating data in a web or mobile environment. Static Server Pages —interactive pages for displaying and updating data in a web environment. The web pages are processed as complete pages. Components for the presentation layer of desktop applications: Forms —interactive screens for displaying and updating data in a desktop environment. Reports —layouts for presenting data in a printed output. Components for the business logic and data layers: Services —components without a user interface that contain operations that can be used locally or remotely. Session Services —service components that manage task-specific behavior, complex business behavior, transactions, and referential integrity. Session services centralize complex business rules affecting multiple data entities. Entity Services —service components that centralize simple business rules for single data entities. Related Links Component A Component is a Main Development Object that defines an executable part of an application. It defines the data structure used to access data, the layout (if applicable) used to present it, and the actions used to modify, validate, and store data. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}